## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the inherent complexity of measuring the indirect effects of terrorism. Additionally, the psychological and social impacts are challenging to quantify and may vary significantly across different demographics and regions. Further research is needed to explore the long-term societal changes resulting from terrorism and the effectiveness of counter-terrorism measures.